<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-849-380  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 849 380.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Oct 30 1989 v10 n43 p37(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DEC sales force said to be lacking.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dooley, Bill.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Complaints are being made against Digital Equipment Corp's salesforce.andP;  Research by analyst Barry Willman of Sanford C. Bernsteinandamp; Co shows customers to be generally disappointed with the qualityof sales coverage.andP;  Since DEC is attempting to enter the mainframeenvironment, an inadequate sales force could pose an especiallyserious problem.andP;  The chief complaint revolved around sales peoplepossessing knowledge about specific products, but not about howproducts worked together as a solution to a certain need orproblem.andP;  Changes have been implemented to ensure that DEC's 100largest accounts are being serviced by a team of sales people whoare interested in selling complete systems, rather than merelymoving boxes.andP;  The company is rebuilding its training program byrequiring an intensive week of briefing for 6,000 sales people, toready them for customer questions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (customer relations).andO;Ticker:    DEC.andO;Topic:     Sales ManagementMarketingCustomer RelationsTraining of Employees.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>